CION Investment Corp. Key Developments

CION Investment Corp. Appoints Joseph Glatt as Director
Jul 12 17
Effective July 11, 2017, the board of directors of CION Investment Corp. approved an increase in the size of the Board from six to seven directors, and thereafter appointed Joseph Glatt, 44, as an interested director for a term expiring at company's 2018 annual meeting of shareholders or until his successor is duly elected and qualified. Mr. Glatt was not appointed to serve as a member of company's Audit Committee or Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee. Joseph Glatt, 44, joined Apollo in 2007 and serves as General Counsel, Secretary and Vice President for Apollo Capital Management, L.P. Mr. Glatt also serves as Chief Legal Officer of Apollo Investment Corporation (since 2014), Secretary (since 2010) and Vice President (since 2009).  Since 2011, he has served as the Chief Legal Officer of Apollo Senior Floating Rate Fund Inc., and since 2013, he has served as the Chief Legal Officer of Apollo Tactical Income Fund Inc. Prior to joining Apollo in 2007, Mr. Glatt was associated with the law firms of Simpson Thacher & Bartlett LLP from 1998 to 2003 and Schulte Roth & Zabel LLP from 2003 to 2007, in each case, primarily focusing on mergers and acquisitions, leveraged buyouts and capital markets activities.


CION Investment Corp. Reports Operating Results for the Quarter Ended March 31, 2017
May 15 17
CION Investment Corp. reported operating results for the quarter ended March 31, 2017. Total investment return-net asset value was 1.60% during the three months ended March 31, 2017. Since commencement of operations on December 17, 2012, total investment return-net asset value is 40.54%, an annualized return of 8.25%. During the three months ended March 31, 2017, CION (i) adjusted its gross share price from $10.10 to $9.57 per share as a result of a reduction of the sales load from up to 10% to up to 5%; and (ii) increased its gross share price two times from $9.57 to $9.65 per share. During the quarter, CION made approximately $161.6 million of new investments and sold or received repayment of investments totaling approximately $172.2 million, resulting in net negative investment activity of approximately $10.6 million.


CION Investment Corp. Declares Cash Distributions, Payable on May 31, 2017
Apr 19 17
On April 18, 2017, the board of directors of CION Investment Corporation declared five regular weekly cash distributions of $0.014067 per share each, which will be paid in May 2017. Each of the regular weekly cash distributions of $0.014067 per share (an annualized yield of 7.58% based on CION's current $9.65 per share public offering price) will be paid on May 31, 2017, to shareholders of record on May 2, May 9, May 16, May 23, and May 30, 2017.


